President Joe Biden welcomed President Pedro Sanchez of Spain to the White House to reaffirm the strong partnership between the United States and Spain. They expressed unwavering support for Ukraine in the face of Russia's aggression, providing continued assistance and imposing economic costs on Moscow. The leaders also discussed the expanded Agreement on Defense Cooperation, enhancing NATO's security. Spain's upcoming presidency of the Council of the European Union in July was highlighted, along with efforts to advance prosperity, security, and the rules-based international order. Economic cooperation in the Americas, climate crisis, sustainable infrastructure development, science and technology, and cleanup efforts in Palomares were also discussed.